[2] Madhya Pradesh, India
Date: Mon 3 Feb 2020
Source: News Track Live [edited]
https://english.newstracklive.com/news/first-death-in-madhya-pradesh-due-to-swine-flu-in-mhow-mc23-nu-1067309-1.html


The 1st case of death due to swine flu disease has come to light in Madhya Pradesh in the new year [2020]. Samples of 29 suspected patients have been taken from many hospitals since 1 Jan [2020]. Two of these patients have been found positive. In the latest case, a woman living in Mhow died of swine flu in her house on 24 Jan [2020]. [She] was admitted to a private hospital on 11 Jan [2020].

The family took [her] home against the doctor's [advice] by discharging [her]. The negligence of the health department has been revealed in this entire case. According to the directive of the government, the swine flu patient should be kept under special surveillance so that there is no risk of spreading the infection, but the health department got information about the woman's discharge after death.

As a precaution, department officials also investigated the family of the woman. Its report is negative. IDSP [Integrated Disease Surveillance Program] branch in charge of the health department, Dr Santosh Sisodia has said that on receiving information, samples were taken for examination of the female patient. On the 2nd day, the woman was confirmed from the Medical College Virology Lab to have swine flu. Samples were also sent to Bhopal. Swine flu was confirmed from there on the 3rd day. The woman was kept on ventilator only.

[byline: Shivani Gite]

